Sure! Below is a script formatted to create a form that accepts and saves user-inputted text. This script uses HTML and JavaScript to achieve the desired functionality.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Security Threats Form</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        .form-container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        input, textarea {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 3px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #007BFF;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 3px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="form-container">
    <h2>Security Threats Form</h2>
    <form id="securityForm">
        <label for="threatDescription">Describe the security threat:</label>
        <textarea id="threatDescription" name="threatDescription" rows="4" required></textarea>

        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>

    <div id="confirmationMessage" style="margin-top: 20px; color: green;"></div>
</div>

<script>
    document.getElementById('securityForm').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
        event.preventDefault();

        const threatDescription = document.getElementById('threatDescription').value;

        if (threatDescription.trim() === '') {
            alert("Please enter a description.");
            return;
        }

        // Save the text to local storage or send it to a server
        localStorage.setItem('securityThreat', threatDescription);

        // Display confirmation message
        document.getElementById('confirmationMessage').innerText = "Threat description saved successfully!";
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **HTML Structure**:
   - The form contains a `textarea` for the user to input the description of the security threat.
   - A submit button to submit the form.
   - A `div` to display a confirmation message after submission.

2. **CSS Styling**:
   - Basic styling to make the form look clean and user-friendly.
   - Added some padding, margins, and colors to enhance the appearance.

3. **JavaScript Functionality**:
   - An event listener on the form to handle the submission.
   - Prevents the default form submission behavior.
   - Checks if the input field is empty and shows an alert if it is.
   - Saves the input to `localStorage`.
   - Displays a confirmation message to the user.

This script provides a simple yet effective way to capture and save user input for security threat descriptions.

